description: This strange tree started to grow vigorously in my yard and was very curious of what it was. It is about six weeks old and approaching 2,5m height. Not flowering and looks as if it’s still growing. Checked with the Department of Agriculture and they confirmed that it’s highly invasive tree tobacco native to Argentina and the interesting question was how did it get to my yard. I had pool construction project that ended around November 2020 and started landscaping and have been buying all sorts of fertilizers from the street vendors of Centurion and suspect the mushroom compost could have been the source of this invading weed. You can see, it loves Highveld, Centurion weather and is very clean. Meaning it has no natural enemies. If it starts spreading it my takeover lots of areas before anyone notices. On a lighter note, I am now curios about the tobacco side of the plant.
